<!DOCTYPE task
  PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Task//EN" "http://docs.oasis-open.org/dita/v1.1/OS/dtd/task.dtd">
<task id="import-html">
  <title>Import from HTML Files</title><prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords><indexterm>Importing data from HTML files</indexterm></keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody>
    <context>
      <p><ph keyref="product"/> offers support for importing HTML files as an XML document.</p>
      <p>To import from HTML files, follow these steps:</p>
    </context>
    <steps id="procedure-import-from-HTML">
      <step>
        <cmd>Go to <menucascade product="author developer editor">
            <uicontrol>File</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Import</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>HTML File</uicontrol>
          </menucascade><menucascade product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">
            <uicontrol>File</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Import</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol keyref="product"/>
            <uicontrol>HTML File</uicontrol>
          </menucascade>.</cmd>
        <stepresult><ph product="author developer editor"> The <uicontrol>Import HTML</uicontrol>
            dialog box is displayed.</ph><ph product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">
            The <uicontrol>Import HTML</uicontrol> wizard is displayed.</ph></stepresult>
      </step>
      <step product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">
        <cmd>Select a parent folder and file name for the resulting XHTML document.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Enter the URL of the HTML document.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Select the type of the resulting XHTML document:</cmd>
        <choices>
          <choice>XHTML5</choice>
          <choice>XHTML 1.0 Transitional</choice>
          <choice>XHTML 1.0 Strict</choice>
        </choices>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Click the <uicontrol product="author developer editor">OK</uicontrol><uicontrol
            product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">Finish</uicontrol> button.</cmd>
      </step>
    </steps>
    <result class="- topic/section task/result ">
      <p>The resulting document is an XHTML file containing a DOCTYPE declaration that references
        the XHTML DTD definition on the Web. The parsed content of the imported file is transformed
        to XHTML5, XHTML Transitional, or XHTML Strict depending on the option you chose.</p>
    </result>
  </taskbody>
</task>